cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.SE 

The paper deals with the problem of identifying new informative features to improve predictive accuracy in supervised learning tasks. This is a common problem in machine learning, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as it covers the core concepts and techniques of supervised learning. The paper also discusses the use of correlation and hypothesis testing, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper evaluates its method on standard benchmarks and a large-scale industrial dataset, which suggests that it may be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
